<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>Lipidomics | PanorOmics</title>

<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;
  overflow-x:hidden;
}

.page{
  padding:72px 7% 42px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.92rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:34px;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:34px;
  align-items:center;
}

h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.3rem,4vw,4rem);
  line-height:.98;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
}

h1 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

p{
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.95rem;
  line-height:1.65;
  max-width:680px;
}

.video-box,
.image-box{
  border-radius:22px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.14);
  box-shadow:0 0 50px rgba(37,99,235,.12);
}

video,img{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
}

.section{
  padding:38px 0;
}

h2{
  font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.6rem);
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

h2 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.grid{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));
  gap:18px;
  margin-top:24px;
}

.card{
  background:rgba(8,15,35,.72);
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.12);
  border-radius:20px;
  padding:20px;
}

.card h3{
  color:#3b82f6;
  margin-bottom:10px;
  font-size:1.1rem;
}

.card p{
  margin-top:0;
  font-size:.9rem;
  color:#94a3b8;
}

@media(max-width:900px){
  .hero{
    grid-template-columns:1fr
  }

  .page{
    padding:64px 20px 36px
  }
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<main class="page">

  <a class="back" href="/">← Back to PanorOmics</a>

  <section class="hero">

    <div>

      <h1>Lipidomics: <span>Mapping Lipid Biology</span></h1>

      <p>
        Lipidomics investigates the diverse lipid molecules that shape membranes,
        signaling pathways, energy storage, inflammation, metabolism, and cellular
        identity. By profiling lipid species and lipid networks, lipidomics reveals
        how biochemical regulation influences health, disease, and therapeutic response.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="video-box">

      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>

        <source
          src="/3_Lipidomics.mp4"
          type="video/mp4"
        />

      </video>

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>What is <span>Lipidomics?</span></h2>

    <div class="image-box">

      <img
        src="/1_Lipidomics.png"
        alt="Lipidomics overview infographic"
      />

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Core Areas</h2>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Lipid Profiling</h3>
        <p>Measuring lipid species across cells, tissues, and biological systems.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Membrane Biology</h3>
        <p>Understanding how lipid composition shapes cellular structure and function.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Metabolic Regulation</h3>
        <p>Mapping lipid pathways involved in energy balance and cellular metabolism.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Inflammation & Signaling</h3>
        <p>Studying lipid mediators that regulate immune responses and signaling networks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Disease Biomarkers</h3>
        <p>Identifying lipid signatures associated with disease risk and progression.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Systems Lipidomics</h3>
        <p>Integrating lipidomics with genomics, proteomics, metabolomics, and clinical data.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
